{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The member of this family from Rhodobacter sphaeroides (Rhodopseudomonas sphaeroides) has been shown both to form a complex with sigma(E) [[cite:PUB00096310]] and to negatively regulate tetrapyrrole biosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>ChrR comprises two structural and functional domains: the N-terminal anti-sigma domain (ASD) binds a Zn(2+) ion, contacts sigma(E), and is sufficient to inhibit sigma(E)-dependent transcription. The ChrR C-terminal domain (CLD) adopts a cupin fold with a conserved PxHxHxGxE motif. It can coordinate an additional Zn(2+), and is required for the transcriptional response to singlet oxygen, a potent oxidant that damages cellular biomolecules and can kill cells [[cite:PUB00048845]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"cdd" {"cd20301" "anti-ECFsigma factor, ChrR , cupin domain"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR02451" "ChrR family anti-sigma-E factor"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Anti-sigma-E factor ChrR", "short" "Anti-sigma_ChrR"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 2, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1025, "taxa" 3811, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3659, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3659, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2756}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR012807", :literature {"PUB00048845" {"URL" nil, "issue" "5", "authors" ["Campbell EA" "Greenwell R" "Anthony JR" "Wang S" "Lim L" "Das K" "Sofia HJ" "Donohue TJ" "Darst SA."], "ISO_journal" "Mol. Cell", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.molcel.2007.07.009", "medline_journal" "Mol Cell", "title" "A conserved structural module regulates transcriptional responses to diverse stress signals in bacteria.", "year" 2007, "raw_pages" "793-805", "volume" "27", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 17803943}, "PUB00096310" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Gre